### readBinaryIdsInternal() {#aa883a589f91024d0a09d1b3c1821ec85}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static Error readBinaryIdsInternal (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorybuffer">MemoryBuffer</a> &amp; DataBuffer, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef</a>&lt; uint8&#95;t &gt; BinaryIdsBuffer, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/amdgpupromotealloca-cpp/#ac760e37eba1d852d0a28011a1a0ce05f">std::vector</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/object/#a4304894bcf353bce5ba4d3dd7ff534d7">llvm::object::BuildID</a> &gt; &amp; BinaryIds, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ae1e26e57357947b25e392fd18ab000db">llvm::endianness</a> Endian)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Read a list of binary ids from a profile that consist of a.

uint64&#95;t binary id length b. uint8&#95;t binary id data c. uint8&#95;t padding (if necessary) This function is shared between raw and indexed profiles. Raw profiles are in host-endian format, and indexed profiles are in little-endian format. So, this function takes an argument indicating the associated endian format to read the binary ids correctly.

Definition at line <a href="#l00095">95</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/profiledata/instrprofreader-cpp">InstrProfReader.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
